    "value": "The Chrome extension **Substital** allows users to add custom subtitles to online videos and supports the following subtitle formats for upload:\n\n- **.SRT (SubRip Subtitle)**\n- **.ZIP (Archive containing .SRT files)**\n\nIt explicitly mentions support for SRT and ZIP formats containing SRT files for drag-and-drop upload. There isn't official mention of .VTT (WebVTT) upload support for user-added subtitles in its documentation or Chrome Web Store listing. Substital is widely compatible with SRT because it is the most universal subtitle format, making it a safe choice for users wanting to add external subtitles to Netflix, YouTube, Disney+, and many more streaming and video sites【3:0†source】.\n\n### Subtitle Formats Explained\n\n- **SRT (.srt)**: The most widely used and compatible subtitle format. Plain text, simple structure, supported by almost all platforms and media players.\n- **VTT (.vtt)**: Modern web subtitle format (WebVTT), supports styling and advanced features, but not always supported for manual upload/extensions like Substital unless explicitly stated.\n- **ASS/SSA, SBV, SUB, etc.**: More niche formats, not supported by Substital — but some other extensions on Chrome do support VTT upload (like YouTube SubtitlePlus)【3:5†source】.\n\n### For Chrome Extensions\n\n- **Substital:** Supports SRT upload directly and SRT in ZIP. No official upload for VTT noted.\n- **Other Extensions (like YouTube SubtitlePlus):** Support both SRT and VTT uploads for YouTube, including features like drag-and-drop, style customization, and bilingual as well as single-language subtitles【3:5†source】.\n\n**If you need VTT upload support in Chrome, consider trying \"YouTube SubtitlePlus\" for YouTube videos, as it supports both .srt and .vtt file uploads. For platforms besides YouTube (Netflix, Disney+, etc.), SRT is your guaranteed compatible format with Substital.**\n\nFor converting between SRT and VTT, free online converters can help if your video platform or extension has stricter requirements【3:2†source】【3:9†source】.\n\n**Summary Table:**\n\n| Extension               | SRT Upload | VTT Upload | ZIP SRT Archive | Notes                          |\n|-------------------------|:----------:|:----------:|:---------------:|--------------------------------|\n| Substital               |     ✔      |     ✖      |       ✔         | Universal, web streaming sites |\n| YouTube SubtitlePlus    |     ✔      |     ✔      |       ✖         | YouTube-focused, dual language |\n\n**References:**  \n- Substital Chrome Web Store【3:0†source】  \n- YouTube SubtitlePlus on GitHub【3:5†source】  \n- Subtitle format guides and converter tools【3:1†source】【3:2†source】【3:9†source】",
